👩🏻‍🍳🎉💕SCRAPPY COOKING EPISODE 20: Crispy Dill Chickn’ Sandwich
.
🤔Stop throwing out your pickle juice. So many ways to use it - in salad dressings, potato salad, caesars’ and MORE. This dill chickn’ sandwich is one of my favorites. It is unbelievable.
.
RECIPE
1 340g block extra firm tofu, frozen then thawed and pressed for 20 minutes
1 1/2 cups pickle juice
1/2 cup all purpose flour
1/2 cup plain, plant based milk
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
1/2 teaspoon paprika
1/2 teaspoon dried dill 
1/2 teaspoon salt
1 1/2 cups bread crumbs
.
.
Freeze tofu overnight. Thaw in the fridge or microwave, then press under something heavy for 20 minutes.
.
Slice your block of thawed and pressed tofu in half, and marinate in pickle juice for half an hour.
.
Preheat the oven to 400F and prepare a baking sheet.
.
In the meantime, prepare your batter. Combine the flour, plant-based milk, garlic powder, paprika and salt in a shallow bowl. In a separate bowl, pour in your bread crumbs.
.
Once the tofu has marinated in the pickle juice, pat it dry, then coat in the flour/milk mixture, and finally the breadcrumbs.
.
Place on a baking sheet, and bake for 20 minutes until crispy. Serve on a bun with your favs or as a main part of a dinner!
.
What scrap next?!
.

👩🏻‍🍳💕🎉EP 19 SCRAPPY COOKING: VEGAN RICE PUDDING (team raisin or no raisin?!)
.
✨We’ve all been in the circumstance of cooking more rice than we need at dinner time. Instead of letting it go to waste - try this vegan rice pudding recipe.
.
🙏I make an effort to research the origin of all of my recipes, and was surprised to see that so many cultures have their own interpretation of rice pudding. I believe this would be most similar to Arroz Con Leche - which originates in Mexico, however I would not say this is an authentic interpretation at all given my use of leftover basmati and vegan ingredients.
.
👇🏻RECIPE:
.
1 cup cashew milk
1 cup coconut milk
1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
3 tablespoons maple syrup 
2 cups of cooked rice of choice (I used leftover basmati) 
.
In a saucepan, add all of the ingredients except for the rice. Bring to a boil, and stir until combined.
.
Add the rice, and simmer for 10 minutes until thickened. Enjoy immediately, or save for later, with your favorite toppings!
.

🍍💕🤯EP 17: SCRAPPY COOKING - pineapple skin tea!
.
🤣Yes this is a pink 🍍pineapple. I found it at my local Costco and couldn’t believe it. It has a slightly sweeter, less sour taste than regular pineapple - but you can obviously make this pineapple skin tea using regular pineapple skin haha.
.
✨IMPORTANT: You want to wash your pineapple skin thoroughly before brewing your tea. Scrub with a vegetable brush, or soak in vinegar for a half hour to remove any bacteria from the skin.
.
🇯🇲Pineapple skin tea originate in Jamaica, where they serve it both hot and cold to aid in digestion. It typically contains pineapple skin, ginger and sugar, and I have adapted the recipe below to have a fall-ish flavor with the addition of turmeric and maple syrup.
.
🍍💕RECIPE:
1 pineapple peel, washed thoroughly
1 knob of ginger
1/4 teaspoon turmeric
1 cinnamon stick
1/2 lemon, squeezed
1 tbsp maple syrup
3 1/2 cups water
.
After thoroughly washing your pineapple skin, bring all listed ingredients to a boil for 30 minutes to an hour. Drain, reserving the liquid for your tea. Enjoy hot or cold.
.

🤯💕🍪EP 17 SCRAPPY COOKING: OAT PULP COOKIES.
.
🥛If you love making oat milk - definitely don’t discard of that pulp! It’s the most fiber and protein rich part, and is PERFECT for these mind blowingly delish vegan oat pulp cookies. I have a great oat milk (non-slimy) recipe on my blog if you google plantyou oat milk!
.
🎉RECIPE .
 1 cup oat flour 1.5 teaspoon baking powder
1/3 cup plant milk
1/3 cup maple syrup
1/4 cup coconut yogurt
1 teaspoon vanilla extract 1/3 cup oat pulp (still slightly wet)
1/3 cup chopped dark chocolate, plus pieces to place in the centre
Flakey salt
.
Preheat the oven to 375F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
.
Combine the dry ingredients in one bowl, and the wet in the other, leaving out the oat pulp and chocolate chips.
.
Pour the dry into the wet and gently mix halfway. Add the oat pulp, and slowly mix until a smooth batter is formed.
.
Add in your chocolate chips, and then separate into approximately six cookies on your baking sheet (about 2 tbsp in size each). Place a piece of chocolate in the centre of each and top with flakey salt.
.
Bake for 11 to 13 minutes and then allow to cool on your counter for 10 before devouring.
.

.

😭💕🌱A secret I’ve kept quiet for over two years. PlantYou: 140+ Ridiculously Easy, Amazingly Delicious, Plant-Based, Oil-Free Recipes is AVAILABLE for PREORDER and published by @hachettego 
.
🙏Starting in 2019 - I set out to create the ultimate guidebook for anyone wanting to embrace a healthy plant-based lifestyle with ease. It had to contain a few vital components: .
- Truly simple healthy recipes for every meal of the day, including breakfast, lunch, dinner, dessert, sides, cheese sauces and salad dressings
- Endless customization options for each recipes based around simple plant-based ingredients almost anyone can find at their grocery store
- A photo with every recipe along with an infographic displaying the ingredients used in my signature PlantYou style
- A kickas$ Foreword by my favorite plant-based physician (hey @theguthealthmd )
- Macros for each recipes, located at the back of the book, so you can use them (or not)
- And a little bit of me (and Tut) woven throughout
.
💕This book is my heart and soul. I poured every ounce of myself into making it the best it could possibly be over the past two years (including taking all of those interior dish and ingredient photos LOL) and I am so so proud of the outcome. I truly believe it holds the power to help people in their plant-based journeys.
.
🙏None of this would have ever existed without your support - so thank you from the bottom of my heart. It is a dream come true.
.
✨As you might not know, PREORDERS are on the biggest indicators of success for a new author. It sends a message to book stores and retailers like Amazon that your book is in demand, it helps massively with media appearances and of course all purchases count towards bestsellers lists. It would literally mean the world to me if you could preorder PlantYou today.
.

🎉💕🥓EP 16 of SCRAPPY COOKING: Banana Peel Bacon! 🍌
.
👌This recipe is loosely based off of my friend @itdoesnttastelikechicken fabulous banana peel bacon creation. Check her out for more amazing recipes.
.
🥰Banana peels are fiber and nutrient packed, but if you don’t want to eat them (understandable lol), they also make an awesome plant fertilizer after composted because they’re so rich in potassium.
.
✨RECIPE
.
1 to 2 banana peels, washed, peeled and sliced into bacon sized pieces (organic)
MARINADE
4 tbsp soy sauce
1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil
1 tsp apple cider vinegar
1/2 tsp smoked paprika
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1 tbsp nutritional yeast 
1/2 tsp parsley 
1 tsp maple syrup
sprinkle of salt
.
Using the inside of a spoon, scoop out any leftover banana flesh from your banana peel pieces and discard.
.
Make a quick marinade using the listed ingredients. Place the banana peels inside the marinade, and soak for at least 10 minutes and up to an hour. Transfer to a parchment lined baking sheet and brush on more marinade to coat.
.
Place in the air fryer for approximately 10 minutes until crispy, or bake at 400F for approximately 15 minutes.
.
Enjoy immediately! What scrap next?!
.

🎃💕🎉IS IT TOO EARLY FOR PUMPKIN? I think not. Here’s my Vegan Pumpkin Spice Latte!
.
🎉Did you know the PSL at Starbucks isn’t vegan? Unfortunately there’s milk in the syrup.
.
🎃I developed this recipe a couple years ago, and since then hundreds of you have said it’s now a mainstay in your fall rituals. I hope you love it as much as I do.
.
RECIPE
2/3 Cup Brewed Coffee
1 Cup Unsweetened Cashew Milk
2 Tbsp Pumpkin Puree
1/2 Tsp Pumpkin Pie Spice
1 Tbsp maple syrup
.
Add all ingredients to a pot over medium heat. Whisk, and heat until warm.
.
Pour in a mug and enjoy with coconut whipped cream on top if desired.
.

🤯💕🎉Ep 15: SCRAPPY COOKING - vegan cheese ball using almond pulp.
.
🌱For the almond milk:
1 cup raw almonds, soaked overnight
4 cups filtered water
.
🔥For the cheese ball:
1 to 1 1/2 cups almond pulp
1/4 cup nutritional yeast
3 tbsp coconut oil
1 tbsp dried parsley
1 tbsp apple cider vinegar
1/2 teaspoon sea salt
.
✨Blend the almonds and water until a “milk” is formed.
.
🙏Drain using a cheese cloth or leotard and transfer the plant-based milk to a clean container in the fridge (store up to 3 days). You can sweeten it with maple syrup and add a little sea salt as desired.
.
✨Reserve the leftover pulp and ensure it is drained as much as possible. Add the remaining ingredients, stir, taste and adjust as needed. With your hands, roll into a ball and chill in the fridge until ready to eat. This won’t be SUPER cheesy but I makes a delicious repurposed spread.
.

🌱🤯💕EP 14 SCRAPPY COOKING: Smoothie BOMBS
.
😉Hey - I see you buying a box of spinach or spring mix at the grocery store every weekend with the best intentions…. When Friday rolls around, and things are looking a bit wilted, DON’T throw them away!
.
👌Blend er’ up with plant milk and whatever greens you have kind of going bad. Pour into ice cube trays and add to smoothies for the perfect cooling effect and more nutrients.
.
✨RECIPE:
2 cups spinach, kale, spring mix (whatever)!
1 cup plant milk of choice
1 avocado (I had one kind of on the edge so I threw it in)
.
Blend, freeze and ENJOY in your favorite smoothies.
.
What scrap or leftovers do you want me to repurpose next?
.

🍓🤫CHIA JAM that might just help you 💩
.
If you struggle with a ✨slow digestive✨ system, you might want to throw some chia seeds in the mix. This amazing raspberry chia jam comes together in 5 minutes with 3 ingredients (and no added sugar)!
.
2 cups raspberries
Squeeze of fresh lemon juice
2 tbsp chia seeds
.
🤌🏼In a pot over medium heat, add the raspberries, and with a spoon crush until they are “mushy”.
.
Add the lemon juice and chia seeds, and mix until combined.
.
Take off the burner when you have a jam consistency, and allow to set for a few minutes. Transfer to a jar and keep in your fridge for up to a week!
.
